---------  Type casting techniques in Python -----

- The process of converting one possible type of value into another possible type of value is called type casting techniques in python .

- In python programming we have 5 fundamental type casting techniques. they are : 
 1. int() 
 2. float()
 3. bool() 
 4. complex() 
 5. str()

 ------------------------------------------
- int()  is used for converting one type of possible value into int type value.
syntax: varname=int(float/bool/complex/str)
✅
❌

- float() is used for converting one type of possible value into float type value.
syntax: varname=float(int/bool/complex/str)
✅ i,f,b,si,sf,
❌ c,sc,sb,ps

- bool() is used for converting one type of possible value into bool type value.
syntax: varname=bool(float/int/complex/str)
- ALL NON-ZERO VALUES ARE TREATED AS TRUE
- ALL ZERO VALUES ARE TREATED AS FALSE
✅ i,f,b,c,si,sf,sb,sc,ps
❌

- complex() is used for converting one type of possible value into complex type value.
syntax: varname=complex(float/int/bool/str)
✅ i,f,b,c,si,sf,sc,
❌ sb,ss,ps,

- str() is used for converting one type of possible value into str type value.
syntax: varname=str(float/int/bool/complex)
✅ i,f,b,c,si,sf,sb,sc,ps
❌


